    "essay_entries": [
      {
        "entry_id": "20767052-41ef-4dc6-b8c0-0a7999394263",
        "essay_identifier": "What excites you about a career in engineering/technology? Why do you think your abilities and skills are a good fit for\nPlaksha's B.Tech program?",
        "raw_text": "I am excited about a career in engineering and technology because I have always been deeply interested in mathematics and physics,\nparticularly their application to real-world problems. These subjects intrigue me because they provide solutions to everyday challenges. By\npursuing engineering, I can implement these concepts in practical ways and use my knowledge to make a meaningful impact on society and\nthe environment through the evolving technology that helps create life-changing solutions. Engineering combines my passion for physics and\nmathematics with creativity, offering numerous growth opportunities and challenges.\nI\u2019m eager to learn, experiment, innovate and grow. I have creative approaches to problems, and I believe that engineering is a perfect fit for\nme as it is as much about imagination and creativity as it is about logic and theory. Collaboration with peers and meeting like-minded people\nwould help me explore and open myself to new ideas and possibilities. I believe my abilities and skills align well with Plaksha's B.Tech program. My enthusiasm for mathematics and physics reflects my logical and\nanalytical approach to problem-solving, which is essential in engineering and technology. Additionally, my love for sports like basketball and\ncycling demonstrates my teamwork, strategic thinking, and leadership skills. These traits would be invaluable in collaborative projects at\nPlaksha. Furthermore, my dedication to sports highlights my discipline, perseverance, and determination, which will help me balance the\nacademic and extracurricular demands of the program.",
        "word_count": 232,
        "placeholder_flag": false,
        "short_response_flag": false,
        "confidence_score": 0.9
      },
      {
        "entry_id": "fba5fb4b-7a0a-407e-904a-fb5c5d3b976e",
        "essay_identifier": "Share a time when you contributed to a project or activity that positively affected your school or community. What\nchallenges did you face, and what did you learn about leadership and perseverance?",
        "raw_text": "During class 11, our newly formed section brought together a diverse group of boys with varying sports preferences. And to make it worse,\nwe had a sports period every alternative day, leading to constant fights between the groups and lots of time wasted deciding what to play.\nInitially, I was drawn to joining one of the sides, but instead, I decided to keep my personal preferences aside and try to find a solution. We\nmade a complete list of what sport everyone would prefer and what they know to play. Though the number of people playing some sports like\nbasketball and table tennis was less, we still decided to manage a solution so as to let them play their choice of sport as well. There seemed\nto be no option, but finally, we arrived at a solution by talking to one other class which had two periods with us and worked out a compromise\nto ensure that each team had an adequate number of players. On the other days, the people playing basketball would join football to keep\nthe teams balanced. This taught me that even if there is no solution in sight, having a little perseverance and out of the box thinking can help\nfind better solutions. It taught me how keeping aside personal preferences for addressing the collective needs can help in the long run.",
        "word_count": 227,
        "placeholder_flag": false,
        "short_response_flag": false,
        "confidence_score": 0.9
      }
    ],
